        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>OFFICE OF THE SUPERINTENDENT.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Jewish Foster Home &#38; Orphan Asylum<lb/>
                Of Philadelphia.<lb/></p>
            <p>Germantown&#44; March 22&#44; 1891.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr. Morais&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>This afternoon Mr. Fleischman<lb/> read to all the children the articles in<lb/> the Ledger and in the Sunday Times<lb/> about your fortieth <sic>aniversary</sic> as a<lb/> Rabbi in Phila.  He asked us to write to<lb/> you&#44; which we are glad to do so We<lb/> congratulate you and hope you will<lb/> be the Minister of your congregation<lb/> for many yeras.  Mr. <sic>Flieshman</sic> also<lb/> read from our Golden Book how you<lb/> asked God&#39;s blessing at the first Foster<lb/> Home meeting almost 39 years ago and<lb/> how during all these many years you have<lb/> loved the children of the Home&#34; So<lb/> we want to thank you for all this<lb/> wishing you good health&#44; much happi&#45;<lb/>ness and a merry Purim.<lb/></p>
            <p>Your loving friend&#44;<lb/>
                The Children of the Home.<lb/></p>
            <p>over<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Jessie Lepcofker for the girls&#44;<lb/> Louis Newman for the boys.<lb/>  We will have a Purim entertainment<lb/> Tuesday and would be very glad if<lb/> you could come out.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
